          "body": "*It will be in that day*, declares the LORD — and seven first-person verbs of removal follow. *I will cut off* horses and *destroy* chariots (military self-reliance, v.10); *I will cut off* cities and *tear down* fortifications (defensive self-reliance, v.11); *I will cut off* sorceries and fortune-tellers (occult self-reliance, v.12); *I will cut off* carved images and pillars (idolatrous self-reliance, v.13); *I will root out* Asherim and *destroy* cities (syncretistic worship, v.14); and finally *I will execute vengeance* on disobedient nations (v.15). The list is comprehensive — every category of trust outside Yahweh is named and severed. The same blade that cut off Israel's enemies in v.9 cuts off Israel's idols in vv. 10-14. The kingdom is not merely additive; it is exclusive. The Ruler who *is* peace will not share His people's loyalty with any rival source of security. The chapter ends with vengeance on the nations that 'have not obeyed' — a final eschatological reckoning that anticipates Revelation 19:11-21."
